  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nCurrently BLS pool size is `number of cores`. I think it should `number of cores - 1` as we use 1 for the main thread\r\n\r\nAlso BLS pool size seems to be always 4\r\n+ On contabo-20, it's really 4: `cpu cores\t: 4`\r\n+ But on hetzner-test0 it's 6: `cpu cores\t: 6`\r\n\r\n(checked with `cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep \"cores\"`)\r\n",
