    "body": "It doesn't really matter too much because in practice seems that only the first 2 workers take all the work. You can't really control on which core each worker will run really.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-03 15-15-26](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/156539251-6dfb617c-26ef-4751-9e36-473df730efa9.png)\r\n\r\nAlso node-exporter shows that load is very evenly distributed across cores\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-03 15-17-50](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/156539596-e53f3c41-4159-4c1a-adc5-fe42fe4f28ba.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
